null, null, null]}, {"name": "SEC. 102. The Administrator of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration is authorized to avail himself of such voluntary and uncompensated services of individuals and the use of voluntary and uncompensated services and facilities of educational institutions as he may find useful in carrying out studies related to climate and atmospheric research: Provided, That individuals and institutions furnishing such services may be allowed reimbursement for travel expenses as authorized under subchapter I of chapter 57 of title 5, United States Code.", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "SEC. 103. None of the funds provided in this Act shall be used to support the hurricane reconnaissance aircraft and activities that are under the control of the United States Air Force or the United States Air Force Reserve.", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "SEC. 104. None of the funds made available by this Act may be used to eliminate or restructure National Weather Service offices.", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "SEC. 105. None of the funds provided in this Act or provided by previous appropriations Acts to the agencies funded by this Act that remain available for obligation or expenditure in fiscal year 2025 may be used by a recipient of such funds to pay the salary of any individual through a procurement contract, for the provision of services by an individual, at a rate in excess of the daily equivalent of the annual rate of pay for level IV of the Executive Schedule under section 5315 of title 5, United States Code.", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "SEC. 106. The National Technical Information Service shall not charge any customer for a copy of any report or document generated by the Legislative Branch unless such report or document contains specific commercial or industrial processes and techniques: Provided, That this section shall not restrict any agency of the Federal Government from charging for specialized services requested by the Legislative Branch.", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "SEC. 107. None of the funds made available in this Act may be used to maintain or establish a computer network unless such network blocks the viewing, downloading, and exchanging of pornography.", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "SEC. 108. None of the funds made available by this Act may be used to acquire any high-impact or moderate-impact information system, as defined for security categorization in the Federal Information Processing Standards Publication numbered 199, ''Standards for Security Categorization of Federal Information and Information Systems'' unless an independent auditor, appointed by the Inspector General of the Department of Commerce or such comparable office, reviews and reports to the Congress on the adequacy of the information security plan for that acquisition.", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "TITLE I\u2014LEGISLATIVE BRANCH", "level": 0, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES", "level": 1, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "Salaries and expenses", "level": 2, "amounts": [null, null, null, null, null]}, {"name": "Members' Representational Allowances", "level": 3, "amounts": [774400, 774400, 774400, 0, 0]}, {"name": "Committee employees", "level": 3, "amounts": [156700, 156700, 156700, 0, 0]}, {"name": "Leadership offices", "level": 3, "amounts": [25614, 25614, 25614, 0, 0]}, {"name": "Other authorized employees", "level": 3, "amounts": [284500, 284500, 284500, 0, 0]}, {"name": "Office of the Speaker", "level": 3, "amounts": [7244, 7244, 7244, 0, 0]}, {"name": "Office of the Majority Floor Leader", "level": 3, "amounts": [2472, 2472, 2472, 0, 0]}, {"name": "Office of the Minority Floor Leader", "level": 3, "am